Phishing Email Examples & Analysis
Email Example 1

Subject: Urgent: Your Bank Account Will Be Locked
Sender: support@hdfc-secure-login.com

Indicators Observed:

Fake sender domain (not official bank domain)

Urgent language to create panic

Suspicious verification link

Request for sensitive information

Classification:

Phishing

Risk Explanation:

This email pretends to be from a legitimate bank but redirects users to a fake website designed to steal login credentials. Clicking the link can result in financial loss and account compromise.

